==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Porte-cochre
<hw>Porte"-co`ch⟦egrave⟧re"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. See <er>Port</er> a gate, and <er>Coach</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A large doorway allowing vehicles to drive into
or through a building. It is common to have the entrance door open upon
the passage of the <xex>porte-coch⟦egrave⟧re</xex>. Also, a porch over a
driveway before an entrance door.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ported</ent>⟦br⟧
